# Simple Docx Report Server


Simple SpringBoot application for generating DOCX files from DOCX templates.

Included:
- source code
- Docker setup files for running application
- PL/SQL example code, how to call it
- SoapUI example how to call it
- Sample template file

How does it work:
Server accepts a JSON document, which is then merged into DOCX document, and returned to client.

## Install

- install gnuplot
- install fonts if not present

## Run
- run it either with "bootRun" task
- or as standalone application
- or inside docker

## Example of JSON:


```
{
	"template":"templates/test1.docx",
	"ext":"docx",
	"NAME":"Some info",
	"SOMEDATA":"Y",
	"SOMEDATA_DESC":"Ok lorem ipsem",
	"LISTX":[
	  {"description":"data 1"},
	  {"description":"data 2"}
	],
	"GRAFZO":{
		"type":"chart",
		"mode":"BarChart",
		"title":"Some chart",
		"width":600,
		"height":600,
		"colors":["0x0000FF","0xFF0000"],
		"categories":["men","women"],
		"values":[10,16],
		"default_font":"SansSerif,24"
	},
	"LOGO":{
		"type":"image",
		"value":""
		},
	"ORGDIA":{
		"type":"diagram",
		"mode":"Organigram",
		"width":600,
		"height":600,
		"colors":["0x0000FF","0xFF0000"],
		"nodes":["H","head","C1","sub department","C2","sub department 2","C22","Security"],
		"edges":["H","C1","H","C2","C2","C22"]
	}
}
```

## How to edit templates 

Images:
- insert placeholder image
- go to menu/insert/bookmark
- add bookmark, that is then replaced from JSON

Fields:
- menu/insert/field
- Mail merge/MergeField
- edit text MERGEFIELD ${NAME}

Tables:
- See sample file

IFs
- See sample file
